{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Adam, Sheth, Enosh,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Kenan, Mahalaleel, Jered,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Henoch, Methuselah, Lamech,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Japheth; Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshech, and Tiras."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Gomer; Ashchenaz, and Riphath, and Togarmah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Riphath: or, Diphath as it is in some copies"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Javan; Elishah, and Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Dodanim: or, Rodanim, according to some copies"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Ham; Cush, and Mizraim, Put, and Canaan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Cush; Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and Sabtecha."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Raamah; Sheba, and Dedan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Cush begat Nimrod: he began to be mighty upon the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Mizraim begat Ludim, and Anamim, and Lehabim, and Naphtuhim,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Pathrusim, and Casluhim, (of whom came the Philistines,) and Caphthorim."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Canaan begat Zidon his firstborn, and Heth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Jebusite also, and the Amorite, and the Girgashite,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the Arvadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Shem; Elam, and Asshur, and Arphaxad, and Lud, and Aram, and Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Meshech."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Meshech: or, Mash"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Arphaxad begat Shelah, and Shelah begat Eber."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And unto Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg; because in his days the earth was divided: and his brother’s name was Joktan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Peleg: that is, division"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Eber, Peleg, Reu,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Serug, Nahor, Terah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Abram; the same is Abraham."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Hadad: also called, Hadar"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now the sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: she bare Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Jokshan; Sheba, and Dedan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these are the sons of Keturah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac; Esau and Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jaalam, and Korah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Zephi: or, Zepho"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Reuel; Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Lotan; Hori, and Homam: and Timna was Lotan’s sister."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Homam: or, Hemam"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Shobal; Alian, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shephi, and Onam."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Alian: also called, Alvan; Shephi: also called, Shepho"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Anah; Dishon."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Dishon; Amram, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Amram: or, Hemdan"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Ezer; Bilhan, and Zavan, and Jakan."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Dishan; Uz, and Aran."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Jakan: or, Akan"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 43,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel; Bela the son of Beor: and the name of his city was Dinhabah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 44,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Jobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 46,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, which smote Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 47,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 48,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 49,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Shaul was dead, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 50,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Baal-hanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pai; and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Hadad: or, Hadar; Pai: or, Pau"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 51,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hadad died also."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah, duke Aliah, duke Jetheth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 52,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Duke Aholibamah, duke Elah, duke Pinon,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 53,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Duke Kenaz, duke Teman, duke Mibzar,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 54,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Duke Magdiel, duke Iram. These are the dukes of Edom."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}